======================================================================
PART 4: REPRESENTATION PROFILE AND SPECTRAL DATA
======================================================================

kind-pasteur showed: sorted (r_S(0),...,r_S(p-1)) determines H.
r_S(t) = |{(a,b) ∈ S×S : a+b ≡ t mod p}|

Connection: r_S is the AUTOCORRELATION of the indicator of S.
By convolution theorem: r_hat(k) = |S_hat(k)|² = Q_k
So r_S and {Q_k} carry the same information!

But the SORTED r_S and SORTED Q may carry different info
because the sorting permutations may differ.

  PAL, p=7:
    r_S = [0, 1, 1, 2, 1, 2, 2]
    sorted r_S = [0, 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 2]
    Q_k = [2. 2. 2.]
    r_hat = [2. 2. 2.]
    Match? True

  INT, p=7:
    r_S = [0, 0, 1, 2, 3, 2, 1]
    sorted r_S = [0, 0, 1, 1, 2, 2, 3]
    Q_k = [5.0489 0.308  0.6431]
    r_hat = [5.0489 0.308  0.6431]
    Match? True

  PAL, p=11:
    r_S = [0, 2, 3, 2, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3, 2, 3]
    sorted r_S = [0, 2, 2, 2, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3]
    Q_k = [3. 3. 3. 3. 3.]
    r_hat = [3. 3. 3. 3. 3.]
